                    </div>
                    <span>I've found three questions in the first exam alone where the answers must be inaccurate - in one case the comment explaining the answer is clearly refering to another question, or an earlier version of the question.
<br />
<br />In general the comments explaining the answers are very short and not very rich in content, so not so useful as a study tool.
<br />
<br />The user interface to the on line tests sometimes requires scolling to read the full text of a question, very distracting.  And it does not let you take tests by knowledge areas.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Not the best</div>
